'''Chemsdine Talbi''' ({{langx|ar|شَمْس الدِّين الطَّالِبِيّ}}; born 9 May 2005) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[winger (association football)|winger]] for {{English football updater|Sunderld}} club [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]]. Born in Belgium, he plays for the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].

==Club career==

===Club NXT===
Talbi was with [[Royale Union Tubize-Braine]] until 2015 when he joined [[Club Brugge]].<ref>{{Cite web|title= 17-year-old star of Club NXT is in the interest of clubs such as Ajax, Wolfsburg, Lille...|url=https://www.voetbalkrant.com/nieuws/2023-01-09/chemsdine-talbi-club-nxt-staat-in-de-belangstelling-van-europese-subtop#ixzz7wxaUDdfO|website=Voetbalkrant.com|date=January 9, 2023|first=John|last=Walckiers|accessdate=March 25, 2023}}</ref> In July 2022 Talbi signed a three-year professional contract with Club Brugge into 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voetbalprimeur.be/nieuws/1039976/officieel-talbi-17-bindt-zich-tot-zomer-2025-aan-club-brugge.html|title=OFFICIEEL: Talbi (17) bindt zich tot zomer 2025 aan Club Brugge|website=Voetbalprimeur|date= July 28, 2022|accessdate=March 25, 2023}}</ref> He started the 2022–23 season playing for [[Club NXT]], in the [[2022–23 Challenger Pro League|Challenger Pro League]], Belgian football’s second division.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://getfootballnewsbene.com/club-brugge-teenager-chemsdine-talbi-on-many-european-clubs-wish-lists/|website=getfootballnewsbene.com|title= CLUB BRUGGE TEENAGER CHEMSDINE TALBI ON MANY EUROPEAN CLUBS WISH LISTS|date=January 9, 2023|accessdate=March 25, 2023}}</ref> He scored on his professional debut against [[Standard Liège|SL16 FC]] in August 2022,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20220819_96075444|title=Chemsdine Talbi (17) wil via Club NXT helemaal doorbreken: "Camera's zijn indrukwekkend"|website=Het Nieuwsblad|date=August 19, 2022|accessdate=March 25, 2023}}</ref> and again the following week against [[Lierse Kempenzonen]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hln.be/sport-in-de-buurt/lierse-klopt-brugse-beloften-tabekou-scoort-eerste-keer-voor-de-pallieters-in-de-voorbije-maand-hard-gewerkt-aan-conditie~a94c09e6/|title=Lierse klopt Brugse beloften, Tabekou scoort eerste keer voor de Pallieters: "In de voorbije maand hard gewerkt aan conditie"|website=Het Laatste Nieuws|date=August 21, 2022|accessdate=March 25, 2023}}</ref>

===Club Brugge===
In February 2023, Talbi began training as part of the first team squad of Club Brugge.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.walfoot.be/news/2023-02-24/un-jeune-talent-integre-lequipe-premiere-du-club-de-bruges#ixzz7wxWqOYKH|website=Walfoot.be|title=A young talent joins the Club Brugge first team|first=Alexandre|last=Fiammetti|date=February 24, 2023|accessdate=March 25, 2023}}</ref>  This was reported as a reward for his playing form.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voetbalprimeur.be/nieuws/1068267/extra-optie-voor-parker-club-brugge-promoveert-talbi-naar-de-a-kern.html|website=Voetbalprimeur.be|title= Extra optie voor Parker, Club Brugge promoveert Talbi naar de A-kern|date=February 9, 2023|accessdate=March 25, 2023}}</ref> He made his league debut for Club Brugge on 18 March 2023 when he came on as a second-half substitute against [[KV Kortrijk]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2023/03/18/belgium/pro-league/kv-kortrijk/club-brugge-kv/3808008/|website=Soccerway|title= KORTRIJK VS. CLUB BRUGGE 1 – 0|date=March 18, 2023|accessdate=March 25, 2023}}</ref>

Talbi would also score his first professional goal against Kortrijk in a 3–0 away win at the [[Guldensporen Stadion]] on 14 September 2024,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/jupiler-pro-league/2024-2025/regulier/07/kv-kortrijk-club-brugge-vanaken-en-talbi-loodsen-club-brugge-in-kortrijk-naar-12-op-12-en-de-leidersplaats~1720024263720/|website=Sporza|title=Vanaken en Talbi loodsen Club Brugge in Kortrijk naar 12 op 12 en de leidersplaats |trans-title=Vanaken and Talbi guide Club Brugge to 12 points out of 12 and the leading position in Kortrijk|date=14 September 2024}}</ref> Four days later, he made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut as a substitute in a 3–0 loss to [[Borussia Dortmund]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/eur/uefa-champions-league/2024-2025/league-fase/01/club-brugge-borussia-dortmund-ondanks-de-harde-0-3-zat-er-meer-in-club-brugge-vergeet-gouden-kansen-te-grijpen-en-kraakt-in-slot-tegen-dortmund~1725022872683/|website=Sporza|title=Ondanks de harde 0–3 zat er meer in: Club Brugge vergeet gouden kansen te grijpen en kraakt in slot tegen Dortmund |trans-title=Despite the hard 0–3, there was more in it: Club Brugge forgets to seize golden opportunities and cracks in the end against Dortmund|date=18 September 2024}}</ref>

On 18 February 2025, he scored his first Champions League goals, netting a brace in a 3–1 away victory against [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]] in the second leg of the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|knockout play-offs]], contributing to his team's progression to the Round of 16 with a 5–2 aggregate win, which earned him the [[player of the match]] award.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2044481--atalanta-vs-club-brugge/ |title=Atalanta 1–3 Club Brugge |publisher=UEFA |date=18 February 2025 }}</ref>

===Sunderland===
On 9 July 2025, Talbi signed for newly promoted [[Premier League]] club [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] on a five-year deal for an undisclosed fee,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.safc.com/news/2025/july/09/talbi-seals-sunderland-switch/|title=Talbi seals Sunderland switch|website=www.safc.com|date=9 July 2025|accessdate=9 July 2025}}</ref> reported to be worth £16.5 million plus a potential £2.5 million in add-ons.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sunderlandecho.com/sport/football/sunderland-afc/sundelrand-transfer-speakman-talbi-fee-confirmed-deal-done-5216420|title=Kristjaan Speakman reacts as Sunderland confirm signing of Chemsdine Talbi for £19m package|publisher=Sunderland Echo|last=Copley|first=James|date=9 July 2025|accessdate=9 July 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=9 July 2025 |title=Sunderland sign winger Talbi from Club Brugge |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cvg6d3jxkyno |access-date=20 July 2025 |work=[[BBC News]] |department=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]]}}</ref> Later that year, on 25 October, he scored his first goal for the club in the stoppage time of a 2–1 away win over [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Steinberg |first=Jacob |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/oct/25/chelsea-sunderland-premier-league-match-report |title=Sunderland flying high after stunning Chelsea with injury-time Talbi winner |work=The Guardian |date=25 October 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Belgium, Talbi is of Moroccan descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20220819_96075444|title=Chemsdine Talbi (17) wil via Club NXT helemaal doorbreken: "Camera's zijn indrukwekkend"|website=Het Nieuwsblad|date=19 August 2022 }}</ref> He played for [[Belgium national under-17 football team|Belgium U17]] in the [[2022 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]], scoring a goal in a 3–1 victory against [[Turkey national under-17 football team|Turkey U17]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under17/match/2034773--belgium-vs-turkey/ |website=[[UEFA]]|date=23 May 2022|title=Belgium 3–1 Türkiye }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under17/news/0275-152af48e1796-8ea947ec8cf3-1000--u17-euro-top-scorers-milosevic-finishes-top/|website=[[UEFA]]|date=26 May 2022|access-date=March 25, 2023|title=U17 EURO top scorers: Milošević finishes top}}</ref>

On 3 March 2025, Talbi chose to represent [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.h24info.ma/sport/maroc-ou-belgique-le-crack-chemsdine-talbi-a-fait-son-choix/ |website=h24info.ma|date=23 May 2022|title=Maroc ou Belgique? Le crack Chemsdine Talbi a fait son choix |trans-title=Morocco or Belgium? The star Chemsdine Talbi has made his choice|access-date=3 March 2025|language=fr}}</ref> On 19 March, after he received his first call-up to the Morocco national team he described it as a "childhood dream come true".<ref>{{Cite news |last=Alami |first=Aymen |date=19 March 2025 |title=Chemsdine Talbi: 'A Childhood Dream Come True' |url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2025/03/185816/chemsdine-talbi-a-childhood-dream-come-true/ |access-date=20 July 2025 |work=[[Morocco World News]]}}</ref>

On 11 December 2025, Talbi was called up to the Morocco squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/morocco-name-star-studded-afcon-squad-as-hakimi-makes-cut-but-diop-misses-out/|title=Morocco name star-studded AFCON squad as Hakimi makes cut but Diop misses out|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=11 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

